# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# ⚠️  COPY THIS TEMPLATE, THEN REPLACE PLACEHOLDERS IN .env  ⚠️
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# This template is safe to commit because it contains no production secrets.
# Keep placeholders in .env.example; never paste real credentials into it.
#
# For local development, copy the template and replace every placeholder in
# the ignored .env file before starting the application:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   $EDITOR .env
#
# Generate strong secrets without committing the generated output:
#   openssl rand -base64 48  # BETTER_AUTH_SECRET (>= 32 bytes recommended)
#   openssl rand -base64 32  # MICX_ADMIN_SECRET_KEY (>= 32 bytes recommended)
#
# CI scans pushes and pull requests with .github/workflows/gitleaks.yml. This
# does not replace reviewing `git diff` before every commit or push.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# TAVILY API Key
TAVILY_API_KEY=your-tavily-api-key

# Jina API Key
JINA_API_KEY=your-jina-api-key

# InfoQuest API Key
INFOQUEST_API_KEY=your-infoquest-api-key
# CORS Origins (comma-separated) - e.g., http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:3001
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# Optional:
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=your-firecrawl-api-key
# VOLCENGINE_API_KEY=your-volcengine-api-key
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-api-key
# NOVITA_API_KEY=your-novita-api-key  # OpenAI-compatible, see https://novita.ai
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=your-minimax-api-key  # OpenAI-compatible, see https://platform.minimax.io
# VLLM_API_KEY=your-vllm-api-key  # OpenAI-compatible
# FEISHU_APP_ID=your-feishu-app-id
# FEISHU_APP_SECRET=your-feishu-app-secret

# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=your-slack-bot-token
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=your-slack-app-token
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-telegram-bot-token

# Enable LangSmith to monitor and debug your LLM calls, agent runs, and tool executions.
# LANGSMITH_TRACING=true
# LANGSMITH_ENDPOINT=https://api.smith.langchain.com
# LANGSMITH_API_KEY=your-langsmith-api-key
# LANGSMITH_PROJECT=your-langsmith-project

# GitHub API Token
# GITHUB_TOKEN=your-github-token
# WECOM_BOT_ID=your-wecom-bot-id
# WECOM_BOT_SECRET=your-wecom-bot-secret

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️  BY production deployment — these control auth and admin secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET must be at least 32 random bytes. The auth module will
# refuse to start (RuntimeError) if this is empty or set to the well-known
# development default ``by-local-dev-secret``. To allow the dev default during
# local development, also set BY_ALLOW_DEV_AUTH_SECRET=1 (and never do this
# with ENV=production).
#
# BY_ADMIN_PASSWORD is the initial password for the seeded admin account
# (BY_ADMIN_EMAIL). Change it after first login.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=replace-me-with-openssl-rand-base64-48
BETTER_AUTH_BASE_URL=
BY_ADMIN_EMAIL=sabar.bao@me.com
BY_ADMIN_PASSWORD=replace-me-with-a-strong-password
BY_ADMIN_NAME=BY Owner

# MICX_ADMIN_SECRET_KEY encrypts the admin secrets vault
# (backend/.deer-flow/admin/secrets.enc). If you lose this key, the vault
# becomes permanently undecryptable and all stored API keys are lost.
# Backup this key alongside any .env changes — it is the only thing that
# can decrypt the vault.
MICX_ADMIN_SECRET_KEY=replace-me-with-openssl-rand-base64-32

# Persistent runtime data
DEER_FLOW_HOME=/data/deer-flow
DEER_FLOW_HOST_BASE_DIR=/data/deer-flow

# Optional: point to repo root on the host for sandbox skill access
DEER_FLOW_REPO_ROOT=

# Model providers
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=your-minimax-api-key
